Talks in Jidda collapse. July 31: Kuwaiti, Iraqi delegations meet in Jidda, Saudi Arabia, to negotiate oil and border dispute. Kuwait and the United Arab Emirates pledge to abide by the agreement. Kuwait goes on state of alert. July 18: Iraq accuses Kuwait of stealing $2. He said that the move cost Iraq $14 billion in lost oil revenue. July 17: Iraqi President Saddam Hussein accuses Kuwait and the United Arab Emirates of flooding the oil market and driving prices down. Here is a brief chronology in the dispute between Iraq and Kuwait over oil production and their common border. 